#. Tag: title
#: circuits.docbook:3
#, no-c-format
msgid "Circuits"
msgstr "Vezja"

#. Tag: title
#: circuits.docbook:6
#, no-c-format
msgid "Placing components"
msgstr "Namestitev komponent"

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:7
#, no-c-format
msgid "On the left, you'll find the <guilabel>Components</guilabel> tab."
msgstr "Na levi strani boste našli zavihek <guilabel>Komponente</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Dragging a component from the sidebar into the circuit will place it under "
"the mouse cursor. Alternatively, you can double click on an item in the "
"<guilabel>Components</guilabel> sidebar to repeatedly add it to the circuit. "
"In this mode, a copy of the selected component will be placed repeatedly on "
"mouse left-clicking until either &Esc; is pressed, or the mouse is right-"
"clicked."
msgstr ""
"Če povlečete komponento iz stranske vrstice v vezje, jo postavite pod "
"kazalec miške. Druga možnost je, da dvakrat kliknete na element v stranski "
"vrstici <guilabel>Komponente</guilabel>, da ga večkrat dodate v vezje. V tem "
"načinu bo kopija izbrane komponente vedno znova postavljena na levi klik "
"miške, dokler ne pritisnete &Esc; ali kliknete z desni miškinim gumbom."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To reposition a component, left-click and drag. You'll find it snapping to "
"the underlying grid. If you drag the component out of the right or bottom "
"edges of the workarea, the workarea will resize itself to accommodate."
msgstr ""
"Če želite spremeniti položaj komponente, kliknite z levim gumbom miške in "
"povlecite. Ugotovili boste, da se zaskoči na spodnjo mrežo. Če povlečete "
"komponento z desnega ali spodnjega roba delovnega območja, se bo delovno "
"območje prilagodilo velikosti."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All components have a notion of orientation; 0, 90, 180 and 270 degrees. "
"Those that aren't symmetrical about an axis can also be flipped. To rotate a "
"selection of components, either right click and select from the "
"<guimenu>Orientation</guimenu> menu, or click on the rotate buttons in the "
"toolbar. The latter can also be accessed by pressing the <keycap>[</keycap> "
"and <keycap>]</keycap> keys (familiar to <application>Inkscape</application> "
"users). The <guilabel>Item</guilabel> sidebar (on the right) provides a "
"powerful method of setting the orientation by providing previews of the "
"components. Flipping components is also only possibly via the "
"<guilabel>Item</guilabel> sidebar."
msgstr ""
"Vse komponente imajo pojem orientacije; 0, 90, 180 in 270 stopinj. Tiste, ki "
"niso simetrični glede na os, je mogoče tudi obrniti. Če želite zasukati "
"izbor komponent, z desnim miškinim gumbom kliknite in izberite v meniju "
"<guimenu>Usmerjenost</guimenu> ali pa kliknite gumbe za sukanje v orodni "
"vrstici. Do slednjega lahko dostopate tudi s pritiskom tipk <keycap>[</"
"keycap> in <keycap>]</keycap> (ki jih poznajo uporabniki "
"<application>Inkscape</application>). Stranska vrstica <guilabel>Element</"
"guilabel> (na desni) nudi zmogljivo metodo za nastavitev orientacije s "
"predogledom komponent. Obračanje komponent je prav tako možno samo prek "
"stranske vrstice <guilabel>Element</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: circuits.docbook:17
#, no-c-format
msgid "Connecting Components"
msgstr "Povezovanje komponent"

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two modes for creating connections (wires): automatic, and manual. "
"These modes are selected via the <guimenu>Connection Routing Mode</guimenu> "
"pulldown menu in the toolbar. Experiment with both - automatic routing is "
"often better for small circuits, whereas more complex circuits may need "
"manual routing."
msgstr ""
"Obstajata dva načina za ustvarjanje povezav (žic): samodejni in ročni. Ti "
"načini so izbrani v spustnem meniju <guimenu>Način usmerjanja povezave</"
"guimenu> v orodni vrstici. Eksperimentirajte z obema – samodejno usmerjanje "
"je pogosto boljše za majhna vezja, medtem ko je za bolj zapletena vezja "
"morda potrebno ročno usmerjanje."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In automatic mode, create a connection by dragging from either a component "
"pin or an existing connection, and releasing the mouse over the desired pin "
"or connection. You'll see the straight-line being drawn turn orange when a "
"valid connection will be created on mouse release. If the line you're "
"drawing is black, it's either because there's nothing beneath the mouse "
"cursor, or you're attempting to connect together two items which are already "
"connected. When flowcharting, the criteria for a valid connection are more "
"complex - but we'll get to that later."
msgstr ""
"V samodejnem načinu ustvarite povezavo tako, da povlečete iz zatiča "
"komponente ali obstoječe povezave in spustite miško na želeni zatič ali "
"povezavo. Videli boste, da se narisana ravna črta obarva oranžno, ko bo po "
"sprostitvi miške ustvarjena veljavna povezava. Če je črta, ki jo rišete, "
"črna, je to zato, ker pod kazalcem miške ni ničesar ali pa poskušate "
"povezati dva elementa, ki sta že povezana. Pri diagramu poteka so merila za "
"veljavno povezavo bolj zapletena – vendar se bomo tega lotili pozneje."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The best way to get a feel for manual connection routing is by experimenting "
"with it. Click on the starting pin or connection, and then extend the proto-"
"connector by moving the mouse away from where you clicked. To place a "
"corner, left-click. To cancel drawing the connection, either press &Esc;, or "
"right-click the mouse."
msgstr ""
"Najboljši način, da dobite občutek za ročno usmerjanje povezave, je, da z "
"njim eksperimentirate. Kliknite začetni zatič ali povezavo in nato razširite "
"protokonektor tako, da premaknete miško stran od mesta, kjer ste kliknili. "
"Če želite postaviti vogal, kliknite levi gumb miške. Če želite prekiniti "
"risanje povezave, pritisnite &Esc; ali kliknite z desnim gumbom miške."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&ktechlab; tries its best to maintain the routes your connections take. "
"However, if dragging a component results in the end points of a connection "
"moving relative to each other, &ktechlab; will be forced to redraw the "
"connection using auto-routing. Before moving a component, you can see which "
"connectors will have to be rerouted - as they will turn gray on clicking."
msgstr ""
"&ktechlab; se po svojih najboljših močeh trudi vzdrževati poti, po katerih "
"potekajo vaše povezave. Vendar, če vlečenje komponente povzroči, da se "
"končne točke povezave med seboj premaknejo, bo &ktechlab; prisiljen znova "
"narisati povezavo z uporabo samodejnega usmerjanja. Preden premaknete "
"komponento, lahko vidite, katere konektorje bo treba preusmeriti - saj bodo "
"ob kliku postali sivi."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:26
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove an existing connection, select it by drawing a small select-"
"rectangle over part of the connector, and hit <keycap>Del</keycap>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite odstraniti obstoječo povezavo, jo izberite tako, da narišete "
"majhen izbirni pravokotnik čez del konektorja in pritisnite <keycap>Del</"
"keycap>."

#. Tag: title
#: circuits.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "Component Attributes"
msgstr "Atributi komponente"

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most components will have editable attributes, such as the resistance for "
"resistors. By default, you can edit simple attributes in the toolbar, when a "
"group of the same type of components are selected. If your selection "
"contains a mixture of different types of components (such as resistors and "
"capacitors), then no attributes will be displayed for editing."
msgstr ""
"Večina komponent bo imela atribute, ki jih je mogoče urejati, kot je "
"upornost uporov. Privzeto lahko urejate preproste atribute v orodni vrstici, "
"ko je izbrana skupina komponent iste vrste. Če vaš izbor vsebuje mešanico "
"različnih vrst komponent (kot so upori in kondenzatorji), potem ne bodo "
"prikazanih nobenih atributov urejanja."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some components have more advanced attributes which are not accessible via "
"the toolbar. These are found in the <guilabel>Item</guilabel> sidebar on the "
"right. The diode, for example, has a variety of behavioral characteristics "
"that you can edit here."
msgstr ""
"Nekatere komponente imajo naprednejše atribute, ki niso dostopni prek orodne "
"vrstice. Najdete jih v stranski vrstici <guilabel>Element</guilabel> na "
"desni. Dioda ima na primer vrsto vedenjskih značilnosti, ki jih lahko "
"urejate tukaj."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is one type of attribute that cannot be editable by either the toolbar "
"or Item sidebar - multiline text. Double clicking on the item will bring up "
"a dialog box where the text can be entered."
msgstr ""
"Obstaja ena vrsta atributa, ki je ni mogoče urejati niti v orodni vrstici "
"niti v stranski vrstici predmeta – večvrstično besedilo. Z dvoklikom na "
"predmet se odpre pogovorno okno, kjer lahko vnesete besedilo."

#. Tag: title
#: circuits.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Simulation"
msgstr "Simulacija"

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, the simulation will be running when you create a new circuit. "
"The status of the simulation is displayed in the lower right of a circuit "
"view, and can be changed via the <guimenu>Tools</guimenu> menu. Firstly - a "
"little explanation on how the Simulator works. This should allow you to make "
"the most out of it."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto se bo simulacija izvajala, ko ustvarite novo vezje. Stanje "
"simulacije je prikazano v spodnjem desnem kotu pogleda vezja in ga je mogoče "
"spremeniti prek menija <guimenu>Orodja</guimenu>. Najprej - majhna razlaga o "
"delovanju simulatorja. To bi vam moralo omogočiti, da kar najbolje "
"izkoristite."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a circuit is created or modified, the affected areas are partitioned up "
"into groups of pins and connections that can be considered independent. Each "
"group is then simulated as a separate entity (although still interacting via "
"the components), with the simulation provided dependent on the group's "
"complexity. Complex groups, such as those involving nonlinear components "
"like LEDs, are slow to simulate. Groups that contain only logic pins, of "
"which only one controls the value on those pins, are the fastest to simulate."
msgstr ""
"Ko je vezje ustvarjeno ali spremenjeno, so prizadeta območja razdeljena v "
"skupine nožic in povezav, ki se lahko štejejo za neodvisne. Vsaka skupina je "
"nato simulirana kot ločena entiteta (čeprav še vedno sodeluje prek "
"komponent), pri čemer je zagotovljena simulacija odvisna od kompleksnosti "
"skupine. Kompleksne skupine, kot so tiste, ki vključujejo nelinearne "
"komponente, kot so LED, se počasi simulirajo. Skupine, ki vsebujejo samo "
"logične nogice, od katerih samo eden nadzoruje vrednost na teh nogicah, je "
"moč najhitreje simulirati."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The results of the simulation are provided through several graphical means."
msgstr "Rezultati simulacije so prikazani z več grafičnimi sredstvi."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The pins on the components will display voltage sidebars. These are colored "
"orange for positive voltage, and blue for negative voltage. Their length "
"depends on the voltage level, and their width on the amount of current "
"flowing through the pin. These can be turned off in the <guilabel>General</"
"guilabel> page of the <guilabel>Configuration</guilabel> dialog."
msgstr ""
"Nogice na komponentah bodo prikazovale napetostne stranske vrstice. Te so "
"obarvane oranžno za pozitivno napetost in modro za negativno napetost. "
"Njihova dolžina je odvisna od nivoja napetosti, širina pa od količine toka, "
"ki teče skozi nogico. Te lahko izklopite na strani <guilabel>Splošno</"
"guilabel> pogovornega okna <guilabel>Konfiguracija</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Hovering the mouse over a pin or connection will display a small tooltip "
"showing the voltage and current at that point in the circuit. Several "
"components also provide graphical feedback - for example, LEDs and "
"voltmeters or ammeters."
msgstr ""
"Če miško premaknete nad nogico ali povezavo, se bo prikazal majhen opis "
"orodja, ki prikazuje napetost in tok na tej točki v vezju. Več komponent "
"zagotavlja tudi grafično povratno informacijo - na primer LED in voltmetri "
"ali ampermetri."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lastly, there is the oscilloscope, discussed in the next section."
msgstr ""
"Na koncu je tu še osciloskop, o katerem razpravljamo v naslednjem razdelku."

#. Tag: title
#: circuits.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Oscilloscope"
msgstr "Osciloskop"

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The oscilloscope can record logic, voltage and current data. The logic probe "
"is optimized for storing boolean samples, and so should be used instead of "
"the voltage probe when measuring logic."
msgstr ""
"Osciloskop lahko beleži logične, napetostne in tokovne podatke. Logična "
"sonda je optimizirana za shranjevanje logičnih vzorcev, zato jo je treba pri "
"merjenju logike uporabiti namesto napetostne sonde."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To collect data, create a new probe component, and attach it to an "
"appropriate point in the circuit. You'll see the output immediately drawn in "
"the oscilloscope. Adding more probes will squash the outputs next to each "
"other - you can reposition these by dragging the arrows on the left of the "
"oscilloscope view, and change their colors via the probe's attributes."
msgstr ""
"Za zbiranje podatkov ustvarite novo komponento sonde in jo pritrdite na "
"ustrezno točko v vezju. Izhod boste takoj videli v osciloskopu. Če dodate "
"več sond, boste izhode zmečkali enega poleg drugega - te lahko premaknete "
"tako, da povlečete puščice na levi strani pogleda osciloskopa, in spremenite "
"njihove barve prek atributov sonde."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:63
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For voltage and current probes, the range of input values can be adjusted in "
"the <guilabel>Item Editor</guilabel> sidebar on the right."
msgstr ""
"Za napetostne in tokovne sonde je mogoče prilagoditi obseg vhodnih vrednosti "
"v <guilabel>Urejevalnik elementov</guilabel> stranski vrstici na desni."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Zooming is controlled by a slider. The scaling is logarithmic; for every few "
"pixels that the slider moves along, the zoom factor will be multiplied by a "
"constant. &ktechlab; simulates logic to a maximum precision of 1 "
"microsecond, and at maximum zoom level, one microsecond is represented by 8 "
"pixels."
msgstr ""
"Zoomiranje nadzira drsnik. Stopnja je logaritemska; za vsakih nekaj "
"slikovnih pik, po katerih se premika drsnik, se faktor povečave pomnoži s "
"konstanto. &ktechlab; simulira logiko do največje natančnosti 1 "
"mikrosekunde, pri največji stopnji povečave pa je ena mikrosekunda "
"predstavljena z 8 slikovnimi pikami."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the scrollbar is dragged to the end, it will remain there as new data "
"is recorded. Otherwise, the position of the scrollbar remains fixed in time. "
"The oscilloscope view can also be moved forwards and backwards by left-"
"clicking and dragging the view. Due to limitations of the underlying widget "
"system, scrolling will be very granular at maximum zoom."
msgstr ""
"Ko drsni trak povlečete do konca, bo ostal tam, ko se bodo posneli novi "
"podatki. V nasprotnem primeru položaj drsnega traku ostane časovno "
"nespremenljiv. Pogled osciloskopa lahko premikate tudi naprej in nazaj z "
"levim klikom in vlečenjem pogleda. Zaradi omejitev osnovnega sistema "
"gradnikov bo drsenje pri največji povečavi zelo razdrobljeno."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right-clicking on the oscilloscope view brings up a menu where you can "
"control the number of times the oscilloscope view is updated. This allows "
"for either a smoother display, or reducing CPU usage."
msgstr ""
"Z desnim klikom na pogled osciloskopa se odpre meni, kjer lahko nadzirate, "
"kolikokrat se pogled osciloskopa posodobi. To omogoča bolj gladek prikaz ali "
"zmanjšanje porabe procesorja."

#. Tag: title
#: circuits.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "Subcircuits"
msgstr "Podvezja"

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Subcircuits offer a reusable and tidy way of using a circuit, when you're "
"only interested in interacting with external connections to the circuit. The "
"subcircuit is creating as an IC, with the pins acting as the interaction "
"with the internal circuit."
msgstr ""
"Podvezja ponujajo ponovno uporaben in urejen način uporabe vezja, ko vas "
"zanima samo interakcija z zunanjimi povezavami vezja. Podvezje se ustvarja "
"kot IC, pri čemer zatiči delujejo kot interakcija z notranjim vezjem."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First, the circuit to be used in as a template for creating a subcircuit "
"from must be constructed. The points of interaction are defined via "
"<guilabel>External Connection</guilabel> components. These must be connected "
"up, and positioned where you want the pin to be positioned on the subcircuit "
"IC."
msgstr ""
"Najprej je treba sestaviti vezje, ki bo uporabljeno kot predloga za "
"ustvarjanje podvezja. Točke interakcije so določene prek komponent "
"<guilabel>Zunanje povezave</guilabel>. Ti morajo biti povezani in nameščeni "
"tam, kjer želite, da je zatič nameščen na podvezju IC."

#. Tag: para
#: circuits.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next, select the group of components and external connections to be turned "
"into a subcircuit, and select <guimenuitem>Create Subcircuit</guimenuitem> "
"from the right-click menu. You'll be offered to enter a name for the "
"subcircuit. Once created, the name will popup in the <guilabel>Components</"
"guilabel> selector under the <guilabel>Subcircuits</guilabel> selection. "
"This can be treated as any normal component - with the additional option of "
"removing it by right-clicking on the item and selecting <guimenuitem>Remove</"
"guimenuitem>."
msgstr ""
"Nato izberite skupino komponent in zunanjih povezav, ki jih želite "
"spremeniti v podvezje, in v meniju z desnim klikom izberite "
"<guimenuitem>Ustvari podvezje</guimenuitem>. Ponudili vam bodo, da vnesete "
"ime za podvezje. Ko je ime ustvarjeno, se bo pojavilo v izbirniku "
"<guilabel>Komponente</guilabel> pod izbiro <guilabel>Podvezja</guilabel>. To "
"je mogoče obravnavati kot vsako običajno komponento - z dodatno možnostjo, "
"da jo odstranite tako, da z desnim klikom na element izberete "
"<guimenuitem>Odstrani</guimenuitem>."
